The US is changing the rules for obtaining a visa
Before talking to the Consulate, the persons must present themselves to the services to apply for visas; the costs will be reduced accordingly.
As from 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa are changed in the United States Embassy and in the Consulates.
For the new procedure, most applicants will have to present themselves before their consultation at the consulate at the visa application service (ASC, the initial letters in English).
The ASC staff shall record the applicant's biometric data, which shall be verified by the consulate prior to the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of the processing of the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counterpart to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for time workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only wish to extend their visas do not need to have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to introduce themselves to the nearest ASC, where they present their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
Since the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second appointment for the conversation in the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those applying for the visa in the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo must no longer pay the service charge of 26 dollars.
You can find additional information on the new visa application procedure in the following web site: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
