In Copenhagen last year, the large emitters such as the United States, China, Europe and others, including Canada, had committed themselves to voluntary reduction plans that would cut global FCKW emissions from 53 Gt to 49 Gt.
However, from this balance sheet, 5 Gt would still have to be subtracted in order to stabilise the climate increase by 2 degrees Celsius from today until 2020, in order to prevent it from being out of control.
In the white glowing pears, 95% of the energy emanates in the form of heat, and the remaining 5% produce the light.
The compact light bulbs reduce energy consumption by 75%, and the new LED light bulbs reduce this energy requirement by twice as much.
