The new LED light bulbs, such as those that the manufacturer Philips has placed on the market this week - this company has participated in the UN study - have a life expectancy of 25,000 hours and consume 80% less energy than a white light pear, indicating the savings possibilities of the exchange plan to be applied in 100 countries.
