Several specialists have indicated that compact light bulbs have reserves, because they contain mercury and that they are therefore to be disposed of as special waste, which is not always possible in developing countries, except that producers provide an acceptance point.
However, according to the report, the main source of mercury emissions on the planet is not the compact fluorescent bulb, but rather the coal-fired power plants that emit much more mercury to produce the electricity wasted by the white-hot pears.
