Furthermore, the hack steak, the tuna from the bush, even the baguette and gum of pesticides and other chemical substances were spilt.
The analyses have revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform in the tap water.
At dinner the salmon steak with 34 identified chemical residues at the "richest" level, and even the plastic plate used to warm up the meal in the microwave was not uncontaminated.
The final risk of this "harmful cocktail" for consumers is "probably underestimated", says the study.
The Alliance Europe Ecology-Les Verts (EE-LV) has proposed to introduce a moratorium on the use of pesticides in order to stop the "increasing of civil diseases".
In July, a study by the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) on the presence of residues of 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals, was identified.
